[{"id": "1l13sxrx7", "chapterId": "linear-programming", "exam": "BITSAT", "title": "BITSAT 2021", "year": "2021", "difficulty": "Medium", "type": "SCQ", "question": "<p>The linear programming problem minimize z = 3x + 2y subject to constrains x + y $$\\ge$$ 8, 3x + 5y $$\\ge$$ 15, x $$\\ge$$ 0 and y $$\\ge$$ 0, has</p>", "options": ["one solution", "no feasible solution", "two solutions", "infinitely many solutions"], "correctOptionIndex": 1, "solution": "<p>Table for equation x + y = 8 is</p>\n<p><style type=\"text/css\">\n.tg  {border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;}\n.tg td{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg th{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  font-weight:normal;overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg .tg-baqh{text-align:center;vertical-align:top}\n</style>\n</p><table class=\"tg\" style=\"undefined;table-layout: fixed; width: 350px\">\n<colgroup>\n<col style=\"width: 132px\">\n<col style=\"width: 76px\">\n<col style=\"width: 142px\">\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n  <tr>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">x</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">0</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">8</th>\n  </tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">y = 8 $$ - $$ x</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">8</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">0</td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table><p></p>\n<p>Table for equation 3x + 5y = 15 is</p>\n<p><style type=\"text/css\">\n.tg  {border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;}\n.tg td{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg th{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  font-weight:normal;overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg .tg-baqh{text-align:center;vertical-align:top}\n</style>\n</p><table class=\"tg\" style=\"undefined;table-layout: fixed; width: 350px\">\n<colgroup>\n<col style=\"width: 132px\">\n<col style=\"width: 76px\">\n<col style=\"width: 142px\">\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n  <tr>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">x</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">0</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-baqh\">5</th>\n  </tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">$$y = {{15 - 3x} \\over 5}$$</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">3</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">0</td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table><p></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1lbwsrcqx/47c647f2-95a1-4a11-a465-54214cffa274/8c37b390-80b5-11ed-a639-815a61f5001e/file-1lbwsrcqy.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1lbwsrcqx/47c647f2-95a1-4a11-a465-54214cffa274/8c37b390-80b5-11ed-a639-815a61f5001e/file-1lbwsrcqy.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"BITSAT 2021 Mathematics - Linear Programming Question 2 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>It can be concluded from the graph, that there is no point which can satisfy all the constrains simultaneously. Therefore, the problem has no feasible solution.</p>", "marks": 3, "negativeMarks": -1, "topic": "General"}, {"id": "m7pup73h", "chapterId": "linear-programming", "exam": "BITSAT", "title": "BITSAT 2024", "year": "2024", "difficulty": "Medium", "type": "SCQ", "question": "If the number of available constraints is 3 and the number of parameters to be optimise is 4 , then", "options": ["the objective function can be optimised", "the constraint are short in number", "the solution is problem oriented", "None of the above"], "correctOptionIndex": 1, "solution": "<p>To optimised $ n $ number of parameters, we need atleast $ n $ constraints.</p>", "marks": 3, "negativeMarks": -1, "topic": "General"}, {"id": "jaoe38c1lrat73xu", "chapterId": "linear-programming", "exam": "CLASS-12", "title": "CBSE 12th Mathematics Delhi Set 1 - 2023", "year": "2023", "difficulty": "Medium", "type": "SCQ", "question": "<p>Solve the following Linear Programming Problem graphically :</p>\n<p>Maximize: $$P=70 x+40 y$$</p>\n<p>Subject to:</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\mathrm{3 x + 2 y} & \\leq \\mathrm{9} \\\\\n\\mathrm{3 x + y} & \\leq \\mathrm{9} \\\\\nx & \\geq \\mathrm{0}, y \\geq \\mathrm{0}\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>", "options": [], "correctOptionIndex": 0, "solution": "<p>$$\\begin{gathered}\n\\text { Maximize: } P=70 x+40 y \\\\\\\\\n3 x+2 y \\leq 9,3 x+y \\leq 9 \\\\\\\\\nx \\geq 0, y \\geq 0 \\\\\n\\end{gathered}$$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lrdzvxdt/16ab7281-e137-4bd4-8a38-0a25a2ef18ac/fd05c310-b321-11ee-9b0f-85e114f86fad/file-6y3zli1lrdzvxdu.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lrdzvxdt/16ab7281-e137-4bd4-8a38-0a25a2ef18ac/fd05c310-b321-11ee-9b0f-85e114f86fad/file-6y3zli1lrdzvxdu.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"CBSE 12th Mathematics Delhi Set 1 - 2023 Mathematics - Linear Programming Question 2 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>Feasible area is OABO</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{array}{ll} \n&amp; P=70 x+40 y \\\\\n\\text { At }(0,0) &amp; P=70 \\times 0+40 \\times 0=0 \\\\\n\\text { At }(3,0) &amp; P=70 \\times 3+40 \\times 0=210 \\\\\n\\text { At }\\left(0, \\frac{9}{2}\\right) &amp; P=70 \\times 0+40 \\times \\frac{9}{2}=180\n\\end{array}$$</p>\n<p>Maximise at $$(3,0)$$</p>\n<p>$$x=3$$ and $$y=0$$</p>\n<p>Maximum value $$=210$$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lrdzxnzf/e23b8ba1-bcb0-457a-89ee-dc3254a658d8/2d6137b0-b322-11ee-9b0f-85e114f86fad/file-6y3zli1lrdzxnzg.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lrdzxnzf/e23b8ba1-bcb0-457a-89ee-dc3254a658d8/2d6137b0-b322-11ee-9b0f-85e114f86fad/file-6y3zli1lrdzxnzg.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"CBSE 12th Mathematics Delhi Set 1 - 2023 Mathematics - Linear Programming Question 2 English Explanation 2\"></p>", "marks": 5, "negativeMarks": 0, "topic": "General"}, {"id": "m6q1wp5t", "chapterId": "linear-programming", "exam": "CLASS-12", "title": "CBSE 12th Mathematics Delhi Set 1 - 2024", "year": "2024", "difficulty": "Medium", "type": "SCQ", "question": "<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n&\\text { Solve the following L. P. P. graphically: }\\\\\n&\\begin{array}{rlrl} \n\\text { Maximise } & Z =60 x+40 y \\\\\n\\text { Subject to } & x+2 y \\leq 12 \\\\\n& 2 x+y \\leq 12 \\\\\n& 4 x+5 y \\geq 20 \\\\\n& x, y \\geq 0\n\\end{array}\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>", "options": [], "correctOptionIndex": 0, "solution": "<p>Given LPP is</p>\n<p>Max $$Z=60 x+40 y$$</p>\n<p>$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\text { Subject to } \\quad x+2 y &amp; \\leq 12 \\quad\\text{.... (i)}\\\\\n2 x+y &amp; \\leq 12 \\quad\\text{.... (ii)}\\\\\n4 x+5 y &amp; \\geq 20 \\quad\\text{.... (iii)}\\\\\nx, y &amp; \\geq 0\n\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m6pv0u1b/2b83528e-3ff9-404c-a22a-20f7031a283f/9e5039f0-e29f-11ef-8d97-1bdf76a53a83/file-jaoe38c1m6pv0u1c.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m6pv0u1b/2b83528e-3ff9-404c-a22a-20f7031a283f/9e5039f0-e29f-11ef-8d97-1bdf76a53a83/file-jaoe38c1m6pv0u1c.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"CBSE 12th Mathematics Delhi Set 1 - 2024 Mathematics - Linear Programming Question 1 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p><style type=\"text/css\">\n.tg  {border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;}\n.tg td{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg th{border-color:black;border-style:solid;border-width:1px;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;\n  font-weight:normal;overflow:hidden;padding:10px 5px;word-break:normal;}\n.tg .tg-baqh{text-align:center;vertical-align:top}\n.tg .tg-amwm{font-weight:bold;text-align:center;vertical-align:top}\n</style>\n</p><table class=\"tg\" style=\"undefined;table-layout: fixed; width: 351px\"><colgroup>\n<col style=\"width: 166px\">\n<col style=\"width: 185px\">\n</colgroup>\n<thead>\n  <tr>\n    <th class=\"tg-amwm\">Corner points</th>\n    <th class=\"tg-amwm\">$Z=60x+40y$</th>\n  </tr></thead>\n<tbody>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">A(0, 4)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">1600</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">B(0, 6)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">2400</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">C(4, 4)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">4000 (max)</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">D(6, 0)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">3600</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">E(5, 0)</td>\n    <td class=\"tg-baqh\">3000</td>\n  </tr>\n</tbody>\n</table><p></p>\n<p>Thus, maximum value of Z is 4000 which occurs at the point C(4, 4).</p>", "marks": 4, "negativeMarks": 0, "topic": "General"}]